import React, { Component } from 'react' import './home.css' {/* Inspirations: mldaneglo.com wlessin.com */} {/* Notes & To-dos:/ - check on https - write a blog on the habits you're trying to build out and rhe scheduule? - figure out how to make a subscription list? - view counter for the website - blog read counter - make it possible to tweet about it, and to like it - fix experience template. Make it be relevant to differnet lables. - clean ouput images, csses etc. - fill out experiences - write out a couple essays. - add links everywhere you think there should ultimately be a link. name them "placeholder" - add colors to experiences - make a diet plannign thing - on "stats" section Add switching to metric Add more stats automatically update stats? */} export default class Home extends Component { render(){ return(

Hi, I'm Fil.


I run bizdev at Pulley. I've been doing judo my entire life, am an avid harmonica player, and am trying to get better every day.


{/*

I run a blog, a podcast, and a bunch of products to make my life easier. If you've got some feedback, ideas, or wanna use anything, hmu!


*/}

I put together this website to share how I'm trying to improve, keep track of what I wanna do, and keep myself accountable.


If you wanna learn more about me, go here. If you wanna see what I'm working on, check it out. My resume is riiiight here.
